# shadcn/ui UI Standards

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements. Do not build custom primitives (buttons, inputs, dialogs, etc.) from scratch when a shadcn component exists.

## Project Setup

shadcn is configured in [components.json](mdc:components.json). Components live in `src/components/ui/`, utilities in [src/lib/utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts), and theme variables in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css).

## Initialization

If shadcn is not initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

Before using a component, check `src/components/ui/`. If it is missing, install it with the CLI:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the component name (e.g. `card`, `input`, `dialog`).

## Usage

- Import from `@/components/ui/<component>`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge Tailwind classes
- Use `lucide-react` for icons (configured in components.json)
- Extend shadcn components via props and `className`; avoid duplicating component source

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

<Button variant="outline">Save</Button>

// ❌ BAD — custom button instead of shadcn
<button className="rounded-lg bg-black px-4 py-2">Save</button>
```
